♪Seven hounds, two whips, one blade♪

10
00:01:15,264 --> 00:01:18,048
♪In rout and flight,
Earth Fiends escape♪

11
00:01:18,048 --> 00:01:20,839
♪Golden Gate seals fast♪

12
00:01:20,872 --> 00:01:25,243
♪South Mountain Hunters
on the righteous path♪

13
00:01:26,752 --> 00:01:37,024
♪South Mountain Hunters
on the righteous path♪

14
00:01:37,024 --> 00:01:41,216
=Love on the Turquoise Land=

15
00:01:41,216 --> 00:01:44,000
(This story is a work of fiction)

16
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:46,960
=Episode 5=

17
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:07,792
(Yan Tuo)

18
00:02:11,088 --> 00:02:14,828
(Yan Tuo, General Manager
of Roadsound Group)

19
00:02:17,072 --> 00:02:18,672
(Legal Representative, Lin Xirou)

20
00:02:21,584 --> 00:02:23,280
(Mr. Lu)

21
00:02:25,652 --> 00:02:27,611
Could you stop rushing me?

22
00:02:28,932 --> 00:02:30,092
The world has changed.

23
00:02:30,411 --> 00:02:32,372
Aesthetic tastes
are growing more unpredictable.

24
00:02:33,252 --> 00:02:34,411
What are you talking about?

25
00:02:35,252 --> 00:02:36,652
Your unmarketable new creation

26
00:02:36,691 --> 00:02:37,851
caught someone's eye.

27
00:02:38,332 --> 00:02:39,131
Really?

28
00:02:40,932 --> 00:02:41,812
I told him

29
00:02:42,131 --> 00:02:42,972
only drafts exist

30
00:02:42,972 --> 00:02:44,291
and the final product isn't done.

31
00:02:44,932 --> 00:02:45,652
Yet he insisted

32
00:02:45,972 --> 00:02:47,812
it's okay and he'd wait.

33
00:02:49,972 --> 00:02:51,212
Don't joke with me.

34
00:02:51,571 --> 00:02:52,652
Not sure if it's a joke.

35
00:02:53,052 --> 00:02:54,611
He prepaid for three pieces outright.

36
00:02:54,972 --> 00:02:55,772
He only wants

37
00:02:55,932 --> 00:02:56,972
to meet you

38
00:02:57,291 --> 00:02:58,372
and discuss art in person.

39
00:02:59,052 --> 00:02:59,972
Who is he?

40
00:03:00,332 --> 00:03:03,212
We can't pry about his background.

41
00:03:03,571 --> 00:03:05,212
Anyway, he's declared

42
00:03:05,652 --> 00:03:07,291
he'll buy whatever you produce.

43
00:03:07,972 --> 00:03:09,731
See? The world has changed.

44
00:03:35,652 --> 00:03:37,252
Are you sure nothing is wrong with him?

45
00:03:37,451 --> 00:03:38,851
A decent business owner.

46
00:03:39,372 --> 00:03:41,611
He started from scratch
through honest work.

47
00:03:41,812 --> 00:03:43,731
Since when do decent people
meet in cemeteries?

48
00:03:43,932 --> 00:03:45,492
It's why he's remarkable.

49
00:03:45,772 --> 00:03:46,451
Think about it.

50
00:03:46,652 --> 00:03:48,731
No invite to dinner
avoids dietary preferences.

51
00:03:48,932 --> 00:03:50,812
No invite to drinks
prevent seeming frivolous.

52
00:03:51,332 --> 00:03:53,972
No office meet avoids formal stiffness.

53
00:03:53,972 --> 00:03:54,812
No gallery meeting

54
00:03:54,851 --> 00:03:57,372
presumes you've outgrown such spaces.

55
00:03:57,492 --> 00:04:00,411
Which place has serene
yet meaningful setting

56
00:04:00,411 --> 00:04:01,812
suitable for discussing art freely

57
00:04:01,812 --> 00:04:03,372
and contemplating life deeply?

58
00:04:03,372 --> 00:04:04,851
Hotel executive lounge?

59
00:04:04,851 --> 00:04:05,731
Too pedestrian.

60
00:04:06,212 --> 00:04:07,372
Can a lounge allow you

61
00:04:07,372 --> 00:04:08,492
to explore life's essence,

62
00:04:08,891 --> 00:04:10,532
human destiny,

63
00:04:10,691 --> 00:04:12,812
or the end of life?

64
00:04:13,891 --> 00:04:14,812
I need to go.

65
00:04:15,171 --> 00:04:16,012
I see him.

66
00:04:22,772 --> 00:04:24,132
Is this how you treat clients?

67
00:04:25,572 --> 00:04:26,652
I'll require a refund.

68
00:04:26,931 --> 00:04:28,731
No need. I won't sell it to you.

69
00:04:28,931 --> 00:04:30,811
Your work is about rebirth, right?

70
00:04:33,572 --> 00:04:34,371
Madman.

71
00:04:39,692 --> 00:04:40,931
Though newly created

72
00:04:41,212 --> 00:04:42,291
with limited impact,

73
00:04:43,012 --> 00:04:44,251
I've read critiques

74
00:04:44,972 --> 00:04:46,291
that mostly interpret your work

75
00:04:46,611 --> 00:04:50,212
as depicting suffocation and confinement

76
00:04:51,051 --> 00:04:52,652
and conveying dark emotions.

77
00:04:54,692 --> 00:04:55,652
If you continue,

78
00:04:55,652 --> 00:04:57,332
you'll expose your ignorance.

79
00:05:01,491 --> 00:05:02,452
Whenever I come here,

80
00:05:03,132 --> 00:05:05,212
I don't feel death or fear.

81
00:05:06,491 --> 00:05:07,572
Your sculptures

82
00:05:07,652 --> 00:05:08,411
inexplicably

83
00:05:08,411 --> 00:05:09,611
don't oppress me.

84
00:05:10,291 --> 00:05:11,892
They evoke childbirth's struggle.

85
00:05:12,332 --> 00:05:14,692
Of course, it's agonizing

86
00:05:15,092 --> 00:05:16,371
for the mother and child,

87
00:05:17,171 --> 00:05:18,012
yet the miracle

88
00:05:18,012 --> 00:05:19,731
of new life emerging

89
00:05:20,132 --> 00:05:21,332
is the ultimate hope.

90
00:05:21,972 --> 00:05:22,491
So I believe

91
00:05:22,491 --> 00:05:23,772
you're fundamentally optimistic.

92
00:05:24,611 --> 00:05:26,452
True, I'm no art expert,

93
00:05:26,731 --> 00:05:27,772
but I'm not pretending.

94
00:05:27,892 --> 00:05:29,411
I genuinely admire your work.

95
00:05:33,772 --> 00:05:35,332
Let me share my interpretation.

96
00:05:35,332 --> 00:05:36,332
I'm all ears.

97
00:05:38,132 --> 00:05:39,332
Outsiders see

98
00:05:39,491 --> 00:05:40,811
a pampered heir

99
00:05:40,972 --> 00:05:42,371
living carefree.

100
00:05:42,772 --> 00:05:44,931
Even you've bought into this facade,

101
00:05:45,092 --> 00:05:45,731
trapped in

102
00:05:45,731 --> 00:05:47,892
an identity and fate you despise.

103
00:05:48,652 --> 00:05:50,452
If you truly appreciated my art,

104
00:05:51,092 --> 00:05:52,452
you'd recognize

105
00:05:52,491 --> 00:05:54,332
the dark emotions, such as suffocation

106
00:05:54,332 --> 00:05:55,452
and confinement

107
00:05:56,411 --> 00:05:57,851
that mirror your reality,

108
00:05:58,811 --> 00:05:59,972
instead of standing

109
00:06:00,132 --> 00:06:01,051
in front of me,

110
00:06:01,171 --> 00:06:02,772
spouting empty praise.

111
00:06:07,572 --> 00:06:09,051
Surprising depth of understanding

112
00:06:09,291 --> 00:06:10,851
for new acquaintances like us.

113
00:06:11,892 --> 00:06:14,452
I have no interest in understanding
a reckless madman

114
00:06:14,452 --> 00:06:15,931
who'd drown others with him in a car.

115
00:06:16,892 --> 00:06:18,452
My apologies. I acted rashly.

116
00:06:18,972 --> 00:06:20,772
I just wanted calm dialogue

117
00:06:20,772 --> 00:06:22,012
and honest communication.

118
00:06:22,411 --> 00:06:23,171
If you still think

119
00:06:23,171 --> 00:06:24,532
I'm mad after hearing me out,

120
00:06:25,491 --> 00:06:26,532
I'll put a stop to it.

121
00:06:26,532 --> 00:06:27,532
No more bothering.

122
00:06:35,772 --> 00:06:36,611
I'm not sure

123
00:06:36,611 --> 00:06:37,892
what you gain from being here.

124
00:06:38,772 --> 00:06:40,212
But this place makes me uneasy.

125
00:06:40,411 --> 00:06:41,132
Get to the point.

126
00:06:43,411 --> 00:06:46,332
I invited you here
to show you a piece of work.

127
00:06:48,212 --> 00:06:48,731
Work?

128
00:06:49,371 --> 00:06:50,012
A tombstone.

129
00:06:59,532 --> 00:07:00,411
A woman

130
00:07:01,611 --> 00:07:02,931
ruined my family.

131
00:07:04,012 --> 00:07:05,572
(Lin Xirou)
She even stole my mother's name.

132
00:07:06,572 --> 00:07:07,332
Lin Xirou is now

133
00:07:08,772 --> 00:07:10,652
in charge of the entire Roadsound Group,

134
00:07:10,652 --> 00:07:11,731
living carefree.

135
00:07:13,291 --> 00:07:16,012
This tombstone was erected for my mother

136
00:07:16,611 --> 00:07:17,972
and will also eventually be hers.

137
00:07:18,772 --> 00:07:21,291
Are you saying your biological mother
was named Lin Xirou,

138
00:07:22,092 --> 00:07:25,371
and the current Lin Xirou
of Roadsound Group

139
00:07:26,092 --> 00:07:27,491
is the one who killed her?

140
00:07:44,692 --> 00:07:45,892
I got you.

141
00:07:46,692 --> 00:07:47,411
Wait a bit longer.

142
00:07:47,532 --> 00:07:48,572
Dad will be home soon.

143
00:07:50,212 --> 00:07:50,811
Tuo.

144
00:07:51,371 --> 00:07:52,572
Dad.

145
00:07:53,291 --> 00:07:54,132
Sorry for being late.

146
00:07:54,371 --> 00:07:55,171
Here.

147
00:07:55,332 --> 00:07:57,371
Happy birthday.

148
00:07:57,371 --> 00:07:59,012
Such a beautiful toy car.

149
00:07:59,012 --> 00:07:59,972
Do you like it?

150
00:07:59,972 --> 00:08:01,851
Yes, I love it.

151
00:08:01,851 --> 00:08:04,051
Who is she?

152
00:08:05,692 --> 00:08:06,371
Honey,

153
00:08:07,532 --> 00:08:08,972
this is Li Ergou's sister,

154
00:08:09,132 --> 00:08:10,772
Shuangxiu. Li Shuangxiu.

155
00:08:12,332 --> 00:08:14,012
Since the baby you're carrying develops,

156
00:08:14,051 --> 00:08:15,772
and there's so much housework,

157
00:08:15,892 --> 00:08:17,731
Shuangxiu will stay here from now on.

158
00:08:17,851 --> 00:08:19,212
Order her around for chores

159
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:20,892
like she's one of our family.

160
00:08:20,892 --> 00:08:22,532
Let me show you the place.

161
00:08:23,851 --> 00:08:26,171
You're about to give birth
and you're still doing chores.

162
00:08:26,171 --> 00:08:27,772
Dashan went to pick Tuo up from school.

163
00:08:27,931 --> 00:08:29,171
I'll go meet them halfway.

164
00:09:08,011 --> 00:09:08,731
Tuo,

165
00:09:10,812 --> 00:09:12,972
I have something very important to do.

166
00:09:14,011 --> 00:09:15,771
Be good and wait here, okay?

167
00:09:36,731 --> 00:09:40,131
Tuo, you may call me
Ms. Lin from now on.

168
00:09:40,812 --> 00:09:41,812
Ms. Lin.

169
00:09:47,491 --> 00:09:48,812
My full name is Lin Xirou.

170
00:10:03,851 --> 00:10:04,771
After that,

171
00:10:05,212 --> 00:10:06,251
she became

172
00:10:06,251 --> 00:10:07,692
the lady of our household.

173
00:10:10,812 --> 00:10:12,371
As a kid, I was clueless.

174
00:10:12,692 --> 00:10:13,771
For years,

175
00:10:13,771 --> 00:10:15,491
I had genuinely considered
her my family.

176
00:10:19,011 --> 00:10:20,371
After I eventually found

177
00:10:20,371 --> 00:10:21,651
my mother's diary,

178
00:10:21,771 --> 00:10:22,611
I realized...

179
00:10:27,212 --> 00:10:28,412
Why are you telling me this?

180
00:10:30,052 --> 00:10:30,972
Gou Ya

181
00:10:31,572 --> 00:10:33,452
was sent to the welfare home
by Lin Xirou.

182
00:10:34,692 --> 00:10:36,092
If he's truly an Earth Fiend,

183
00:10:37,251 --> 00:10:38,972
then Lin Xirou must control the key

184
00:10:39,052 --> 00:10:40,891
to transforming Earth Fiends
into human form.

185
00:10:42,292 --> 00:10:43,452
What else do you know?

186
00:10:43,812 --> 00:10:46,172
I've looked for a long time.
But she's too cautious.

187
00:10:47,292 --> 00:10:48,491
She has guarded against me.

188
00:10:49,292 --> 00:10:50,172
I found nothing.

189
00:10:50,812 --> 00:10:52,412
But now that Gou Ya is in trouble

190
00:10:52,932 --> 00:10:53,851
and I've met you

191
00:10:54,011 --> 00:10:55,172
and your organization,

192
00:10:55,771 --> 00:10:56,851
it gives me hope.

193
00:10:57,851 --> 00:10:58,972
I just want to know

194
00:10:58,972 --> 00:11:00,092
what I should do

195
00:11:00,371 --> 00:11:02,092
(Lin Xirou)
to avenge my mother.

196
00:11:03,651 --> 00:11:05,011
First, you need to find out

197
00:11:05,212 --> 00:11:06,572
exactly what Lin Xirou is.

198
00:11:06,891 --> 00:11:08,131
I don't care what she is.

199
00:11:09,891 --> 00:11:11,292
But I'm certain

200
00:11:11,531 --> 00:11:13,292
her connection
to Earth Fiends is unusual.

201
00:11:14,651 --> 00:11:15,851
If you truly oppose

202
00:11:15,851 --> 00:11:16,731
the Earth Fiends,

203
00:11:17,011 --> 00:11:17,771
working with me

204
00:11:18,371 --> 00:11:19,731
is a golden opportunity.

205
00:11:21,052 --> 00:11:23,731
You said it you considered
her your family.

206
00:11:23,891 --> 00:11:25,052
And she raised you.

207
00:11:26,011 --> 00:11:27,611
Do you think I'll take such a risk

208
00:11:27,731 --> 00:11:28,692
by working with you?

209
00:11:29,172 --> 00:11:31,292
If a hunter teams up with a wolf cub,

210
00:11:31,332 --> 00:11:32,972
they could destroy the entire wolf den.

211
00:11:32,972 --> 00:11:34,131
Isn't that worth the gamble?

212
00:11:34,332 --> 00:11:35,771
Don't flatter yourself as a wolf.

213
00:11:36,212 --> 00:11:38,332
You could be the snake
in the farmer's story.

214
00:11:41,371 --> 00:11:41,851
Fine.

215
00:11:43,692 --> 00:11:46,131
I know you're not afraid
of snakes or wolves.

216
00:11:48,011 --> 00:11:49,572
But you're afraid of water.

217
00:11:51,092 --> 00:11:53,251
I also know your home address
and workplace.

218
00:11:53,412 --> 00:11:54,932
Even your artistic philosophy.

219
00:11:55,692 --> 00:11:56,972
Driving a car into water

220
00:11:57,611 --> 00:11:58,572
was me going too far.

221
00:11:59,092 --> 00:12:00,412
But I can't promise

222
00:12:00,412 --> 00:12:01,812
I won't do it again.

223
00:12:08,212 --> 00:12:10,011
You're truly something.

224
00:12:10,771 --> 00:12:12,651
How rare to hear you say something kind.

225
00:12:13,491 --> 00:12:14,412
What do you mean?

226
00:12:16,052 --> 00:12:17,891
After hearing your life story earlier,

227
00:12:18,212 --> 00:12:19,172
I genuinely felt

228
00:12:19,172 --> 00:12:20,851
a slight sense of empathy.

229
00:12:21,251 --> 00:12:22,172
I even forgot about

230
00:12:22,172 --> 00:12:23,251
our past unpleasantness.

231
00:12:24,011 --> 00:12:24,932
But just now

232
00:12:25,011 --> 00:12:26,212
your words

233
00:12:26,491 --> 00:12:28,531
revived my disgust toward you.

234
00:12:29,251 --> 00:12:30,412
You have a way with people.

235
00:12:31,771 --> 00:12:32,891
If that's the case,

236
00:12:33,092 --> 00:12:34,651
your being immune to all persuasion

237
00:12:34,651 --> 00:12:35,812
and your sarcastic skills

238
00:12:35,812 --> 00:12:36,972
are thoroughly impressive.

239
00:12:37,812 --> 00:12:39,092
A truly dedicated

240
00:12:39,092 --> 00:12:40,572
and virtuous artist.

241
00:12:44,972 --> 00:12:45,572
Come with me.

242
00:12:46,172 --> 00:12:46,851
To where?

243
00:12:47,851 --> 00:12:49,491
I'll show you a sculpture.

244
00:13:13,078 --> 00:13:17,332
(Temple of the Righteous Lord)

245
00:13:17,332 --> 00:13:18,452
In ancient times,

246
00:13:19,052 --> 00:13:22,131
a meteor fell
into South Mountain's ancient woods.

247
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:24,371
The meteor melted into the earth,

248
00:13:24,611 --> 00:13:25,771
turning the soil turquoise.

249
00:13:26,692 --> 00:13:30,212
Plants and animals mutated,
and strange occurrences multiplied.

250
00:13:31,092 --> 00:13:34,611
Then a type of light-fearing,

251
00:13:35,572 --> 00:13:36,651
carnivorous savage beasts

252
00:13:36,651 --> 00:13:38,172
started roaming South Mountain.

253
00:13:39,371 --> 00:13:40,812
The locals

254
00:13:40,932 --> 00:13:42,812
named those beasts Earth Fiends.

255
00:13:43,371 --> 00:13:45,731
Earth Fiends were brutal killers.

256
00:13:45,812 --> 00:13:47,131
People suffered terribly.

257
00:13:48,332 --> 00:13:48,972
Later,

258
00:13:49,692 --> 00:13:51,172
the emperor sent troops

259
00:13:51,692 --> 00:13:53,491
to drive the Earth Fiends underground.

260
00:13:54,572 --> 00:13:56,172
The soldiers who stayed

261
00:13:56,812 --> 00:13:58,611
abandoned their identities

262
00:13:58,891 --> 00:14:00,692
and called themselves
South Mountain Hunters.

263
00:14:00,692 --> 00:14:02,292
and swore enmity with Earth Fiends.

264
00:14:02,452 --> 00:14:03,731
This legacy continues today.

265
00:14:06,812 --> 00:14:08,011
Such detailed settings?

266
00:14:08,212 --> 00:14:09,572
Not writing a novel wastes them.

267
00:14:09,692 --> 00:14:10,851
I've said my piece.

268
00:14:11,651 --> 00:14:12,731
Believe what you will.

269
00:14:14,611 --> 00:14:15,212
Go on.

270
00:14:16,251 --> 00:14:17,572
Those injured by Earth Fiends

271
00:14:17,932 --> 00:14:19,092
develop filmy tissue

272
00:14:19,371 --> 00:14:21,371
over wounds after some time,

273
00:14:21,812 --> 00:14:23,011
like rooting and sprouting.

274
00:14:23,771 --> 00:14:25,412
Though revealing this to an outsider

275
00:14:25,771 --> 00:14:26,651
breaks our rules,

276
00:14:27,172 --> 00:14:28,531
soon I'll also be an outsider.

277
00:14:28,531 --> 00:14:29,332
It doesn't matter.

278
00:14:30,572 --> 00:14:31,371
Besides,

279
00:14:32,131 --> 00:14:33,172
what I described earlier

280
00:14:33,172 --> 00:14:34,611
were beast-like Earth Fiends.

281
00:14:35,491 --> 00:14:37,651
Humanoid ones might differ entirely.

282
00:14:38,172 --> 00:14:39,011
So

283
00:14:39,692 --> 00:14:41,651
you're also a South Mountain Hunter,

284
